The first night its always be a Full Moon so be ready and safe by the time night fall.

During a Full Moon 5 Additional mobs have the ability to spawn. These are very powerfull mobs.

Full Moons happens every 2 hours and 30 minutes of gameplay.

This event has a 10% chance to occurr every night.
When this event happens, a message will be displayed in chat.

The special mobs that have the ability to spawn during this event have a change to drop Realmstones of The Abyss.

Starting message:
"The Hunt for Blood has Begun"

The Abyss is a dropped by Tricksters.

This Realmstone can be used to travel to The Abyss Dimension.

The Big Day event has a 5% chance to occurr every day.
When this event happens, a message will be displayed in chat.

Starting message:
"Today is a big day."

Ending message:
"The ground settles as the sun sets."

During this event additional mobs have the ability to spawn. These are very powerfull mobs.
Can be obtained as a drop from the Scrubby.
Can be obtained as a drop from the Dark Beast.

Visit Lunalus.

Info:
Lunalus is a space like dimension with floating moons and mysterious structures.

Hunter Level Recommended: 15

There are a total of 7 different Events:

Notes:
The first night will always be a Full Moon Event night.

Night Events:
- Full Moon
- Bloodhunt 
- Soul Scurry
- Lunar

Day Events:
- Death Day
- Creep Day
- Big Day

The Death Day event has a 4% chance to occurr every day.
When this event happens, a message will be displayed in chat.

Starting message:
"Today is a good day to die."

Ending message:
"The day of death has ended."

During this event additional mobs have the ability to spawn. These are very powerfull mobs.

The Lunar event has a 6.67% chance to occurr every night.
When this event happens, a message will be displayed in chat.

Starting message:
"The world just got stranger."

Ending message:
"The strange creatures begin to vanish."

During this event additional mobs have the ability to spawn. These are very powerfull mobs.

The Soul Scurry event has a 8.3% chance to occurr every night.
When this event happens, a message will be displayed in chat.

Starting message:
"Lost souls scurry across the world in the darkness"

Ending message:
"The lost souls fade as the sun comes up"

During this event additional mobs have the ability to spawn. These are very powerfull mobs.

The Creep Day event has a 5% chance to occurr every day.
When this event happens, a message will be displayed in chat.

Starting message:
"The hissing sounds begin."

Ending message:
"The hissing fades away."

During this event additional mobs have the ability to spawn. These are very powerfull mobs.

The Immortallis RealmStone is a drop from the Death Hunter.

This Realmstone can be used to travel to the Immortallis Dimension.

It is recommended to find a biome with low spawn rate of hostile mobs.

Recommended Biomes:
- Roofed Forest
- Jungle
- Mushroom Island

Biomes to avoid:
- Taiga
- Beach
- Ice Plains
- Savanna
- Swamps
- Plains
- Extreme Hills

The first night of the game will always be a Full Moon Event, make sure to have a safe place by night and make use of the Full Moon event to collect more scrolls and weapons.

Or you can just get a bed and skip the night.

During a Full Moon Event 5 Additional Mobs have the ability to spawn. These are very powerfull mobs.

"In Minecraft the moon goes through a Lunar Cycle. Each Lunar Cycle consists of 8 moon phases; on the 8th moon phase, the Full Moon comes out."

The Resource Systems provide different Resources that aid the player.

Quests are in the same order as how they show in the "HUD" from left to right.

Tribute:

Allows the player to obtain buffs at night.

"The tribute resource exists between energy and battle rage. Tribute is divided into four bars, each bar representing one of the gods in the mod. The bars start out gray and if the player gains tribute points, will become filled with color. Each bar is a different color."

"In the overworld, ancient cavern, and immortallis, the bars are empty and the player has the ability to fill them."

"In the overworld, the bars are filled by repeatedly performing certain activities. The bars will only fill if the player has performed the activities during the day. The activities needed to fill the bars are listed below. Note that some bars will actually go down if the player performs other activities.

Selyan - To fill the green bar, the player must harvest at least 50 crops.

Luxon - To fill the blue bar, the player must use at least 50 essences on an ascension shrine (essence type doesn't matter), or capture pixons with a stone bowl. The blue bar will go down if the player defeats mobs with melee weapons.

Erebon - To fill the red bar, the player must defeat at least 50 mobs with melee weapons.

Pluton - To fill the yellow bar, the player must acquire drops from foraging or logging, or harvest 100 items from an extraction device. The amount of items harvested from foraging/logging depends on the player's level."

Battle Rage:

Allows the player to do critical hits.

Info:
When used up, it will being regenerating naturally.

Energy:

Used as ammo for some weapons.

Info:
When used up, it will being regenerating naturally.

Weapons:
- Energy Weapons
- Scythes

Creation:

Used to summon Minions.

Info:
When used up, it will being regenerating naturally.

It is used up when the player uses a Minion Staff, a Shadowlord Staff or a Hive Staff.

Soul Power:

Used to provide power to Tablets.

Info:
When used up, it will being regenerating naturally.

Butchery is a skill based around attacking mobs.

Info:
Every mob has 1 in 30 change of spawning a Blood Lust after getting killed.
Use a Blood Accumulator to capture Blood Lusts.

Expedition is a skill based around sprinting.

Info:
It is increased every 4 seconds of player sprinting.

Extraction is a skill themed around extracting resources from lava.

Info:
To increase it the player will need an Extraction Device.

"First, the player must fill the extraction device with lava by placing lava on top of it. An example of what this should look like can be seen in the picture (right). Once the device is filled, the player must use either a stone bowl or diamond bowl on the filled device to extract an item from it.

How to train Extraction.
Once the player has used the bowl on the device, the lava on top will disappear, and a block of obsidian will appear under the device. The obsidian will have to be removed to use the device again.

Upon using the device, the player has a 33% chance to actually find an item, otherwise finding nothing. As the player levels up in extraction, more items become available."

Loggin is a skill based around chopping down trees.

Info:
Can be increased by breaking log blocks.

The Acnient Teleporter is a portal require to travel to most dimensions with the exception of Greckon, Runandor and Lunalus.

Create a portal:
"The player must build the frame to be 5 blocks long and 6 blocks tall, and all of the above listed materials must be present in the portal structure.
The Carved Rune of Power has to go in the center spot on the bottom of the portal frame. 
The rest of the carved runes can go anywhere. The corners are not optional"

Activate a portal:
"Realmstones are used to activate the portal. To activate the portal with a realmstone, the player has to use the realmstone on the Carved Rune of Power in the portal structure."

Materials location.
"The ancient rock can be found in a ruined teleporter structure, while the carved runes (except carved rune of power) can be found inside vanilla chests in structures (Dungeons, Mineshafts, Village Blacksmiths, etc), and uncommonly as a part of the ruined teleporter. The carved rune of power is an exception, it must be crafted instead of found."
